 1. The Type I Telecommunications Market (Revenues). a. 
The Market Scale of Domestic Telecommunications for FY1992 
&lt;annot&gt; Notes: 1. As for the telephone and leased circuit 
services for JR companies, these revenues of the Japan Telecom 
Co., Ltd. which provide telecommunications services for JR, are 
not included. 2. Figures on NTT's telephone revenues exclude 
mobile phone and ship telephone revenues. 3. Percentages in 
parentheses represent NCCs' share. 4. Percentages above the 
arrows represent annual growth rates. 5. The portable telephone 
revenues are included in the Mobile Phone revenues. 6. 
Parenthetical figures in NTT's FY92 revenues represent revenues 
of NTT Mobile Communications Network, Inc. 7. Figures in 
subtotals and totals are calculated in &yen;1 million units, and 
after the calculation, yen portions less than &yen;100 million 
are omitted. 8. ``Others'' include telex, telegram, data 
communications, convenience radio phone, facsimile 
communications.&lt;/graphic&gt; 


<FIG ID=JPRS-JST-028L-47A>      C. (Part Two) b. The Market Scale of International Telecommunications for FY1992 </FIG>

&lt;annot&gt; Notes: 1. Percentages in parentheses represent NCCs' 
share. 2. Percentages above the arrows represent annual growth 
rates. 3. The symbol _D_ denotes a decrease. 4. Figures in 
subtotals and totals are calculated in &yen;1 million units, and 
after the calculation, yen portions less than &yen;100 million 
are omitted. 5. ``Others'' include maritime satellite telex, 
international facsimile communications. 6. ``Total'' represents 
telecommunications services operating revenues.&lt;/graphic&gt; 


